cs.SI, cs.GT, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the representation of measures of network centrality using a social network representation and cooperative skill games. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.SI is the most likely category as it directly relates to social network representation, while cs.GT and cs.SOC are also likely given the discussion of cooperative skill games and network centrality measures. cs.DS and cs.AI are less likely but still possible given the computational and algorithmic aspects of the paper.
